The paper deals with the problem of removing ink markers from histopathology whole slide images using convolutional neural networks. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also involves image restoration and classification, which are relevant to the information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. The use of deep learning models for classification and image generation also suggests a connection to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
